cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses the development of learning-based driver models using naturalistic driving data, which involves machine learning techniques such as Gaussian Mixture Model (GMM) and Hidden Markov Model (HMM). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on the development of advanced driver assistance systems and automated driving systems, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the use of GMM and Probability Density Functions (PDF) suggests the involvement of computer vision techniques, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the statistical analysis of the fitting results, which involves the use of statistical methods and algorithms, and hence falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
